`method` `Table.cast`
    
    
    cast(col_name, dtype, optional=False)
    

Casts a column to a specific data type. This can be one of the normal python classes, an internal W&B type, or an example object, like an instance of wandb.Image or wandb.Classes. **Args:**

  * `col_name` (str): The name of the column to cast.
  * `dtype` (class, wandb.wandb_sdk.interface._dtypes.Type, any): The target dtype.
  * `optional` (bool): If the column should allow Nones.



